---
import ServiceLayout from '../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Pricing | Flat-Fee Estate Planning | Mesa Estate Planning"
  description="Mesa Estate Planning offers flat-fee estate planning — no hourly billing, no surprises. Your fee is quoted after a free consultation so you know the total cost before committing."
  heroTitle="Clear pricing. No surprises."
  heroSubtitle="All of our work is flat-fee, quoted after your free consultation. You know exactly what you're paying before you commit to anything."
  breadcrumbParent="About"
  breadcrumbParentUrl="/about"
>
  <div class="quick-answer">
    <div class="quick-answer-label">Quick Answer</div>
    <p>Mesa Estate Planning uses flat-fee pricing for all estate planning work. Your fee is quoted after a free 30-minute consultation once we understand your situation. There are no hourly charges, no retainer surprises, and no hidden costs. You know the total before you agree to anything.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>How Our Pricing Works</h2>
    <p>We don't quote fees over the phone or on a website, and that's intentional. Estate planning isn't one-size-fits-all — a single individual with straightforward assets needs a different plan than a married couple with a business, rental properties, and children from prior marriages. Quoting a number before understanding the situation means either overcharging simple cases or underdelivering on complex ones.</p>

    <p>Here's how it works instead:</p>

    <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> You book a <a href="/contact">free consultation</a>. This takes about 30 minutes and costs nothing.</p>
    <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> We review your situation and prepare a written recommendation that explains what documents we're proposing and why.</p>
    <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> We quote a flat fee for the recommended plan. You see the total cost before you commit to anything.</p>

    <p>No hourly billing. No invoices that grow beyond the original quote. The fee covers the full process from drafting through signing, including revisions and funding guidance.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>What's Included</h2>
    <p>Every engagement includes the initial consultation, document drafting, a review period where you can request changes, the signing meeting with notarization, and written funding guidance for trust-based plans. We don't charge extra for phone calls, emails, or revisions during the process.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-section">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can you give me a rough range of what estate planning costs?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The cost depends on the complexity of your situation. A straightforward plan for a single individual will cost less than a plan for a couple with business interests, blended family considerations, and tax planning needs. The free consultation is designed to give you a clear picture of what you need and what it will cost — with no obligation to proceed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Do you offer payment plans?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We can discuss payment arrangements during the consultation. We want to make sure cost isn't the thing that stops someone from protecting their family.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What if my situation changes after the plan is signed?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Amendments and updates are quoted separately as needed, also at a flat fee. We recommend reviewing your plan after any major life event and every three to five years. Existing clients get priority scheduling and straightforward pricing for updates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ServiceLayout>
